The Reverse State monad for some set of states S can be represented by the monad container S \to  S \triangleright  \lambda  \_ . S with the data:
       \begin {align*}       \iota  &:= \lambda  x . x\\       \sigma \ f\ g &:= \lambda  s . f\ (\pi _2\ (g^\circlearrowright \ s))\\       \text {pr}\ \{f\}\ \{g\}\ s &:= (\pi _2\ (g^\circlearrowright \ s) , s)     \end {align*}   
  Where we use the notation:
       \begin {align*}       -^\circlearrowright  &: (S \to  S \to  S) \to  S \to  (S \to  S) \times  S\\       f^\circlearrowright \ s &:= \text {fix}\ (f' , s'') . (f\ s'', f'\ s)     \end {align*}   
  This is only definable in a theory with unrestricted fixed points; f^\circlearrowright  may be undefined.

