504mhe-0006mhe-0006.xmlSimple type environmentsDefinition2024124Chris PurdyReuben Rowe
Simple type environments, denoted \mathcal {H}, are finite partial maps from expression variables to tuples of a variance annotation and a domain.
When \mathcal {H}(x) is undefined for all x we say \mathcal {H} is empty.
  Abusing notation, we write x^v : T \in  \mathcal {H} to mean \mathcal {H}(x) = (v , T), and \mathcal {H} \subseteq  \mathcal {H}^\prime  to mean that x^v : T \in  \mathcal {H} implies x^v : T \in  \mathcal {H}^\prime .
